{"id":773,"parent_id":0,"book_id":8,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":773,"title":"Leaven","subtitle":"","short_title":"Leaven","uri":"/scriptures/bd/leaven","content":[["div",{"id":"t1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/leaven.t1","order":".000.2045"},[".title","Leaven"],["div",{"id":"p1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/leaven.p1","order":".000.2046"},"Anything that in cooking produces fermentation, a lump of old dough being generally used. No leaven was allowed during the Passover Feast (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ex/12.15,19"},"Ex. 12:15, 19"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ex/13.7"},"13:7"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/deut/16.4"},"Deut. 16:4"],") or in offerings made to God with fire (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ex/29.2"},"Ex. 29:2"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/lev/2.11"},"Lev. 2:11"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/lev/7.12"},"7:12"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/num/6.15"},"Num. 6:15"],"). It was probably forbidden because there was associated with it the idea of corruption. In the New Testament it was as a rule symbolic of sin (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/16.6"},"Matt. 16:6"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/8.15"},"Mark 8:15"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/12.1"},"Luke 12:1"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/1-cor/5.7"},"1Â Cor. 5:7"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/gal/5.9"},"Gal. 5:9"],"); but in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/13.33"},"Matt. 13:33"],"it is compared to the inward growth and influence of the kingdom of heaven (church) upon the earth."]]],"refs":null}
